    "transcription_text": "The Wall Street Journal also found that managed ESG funds cost five to 15 times as much in fees when compared to an index fund. Mir Statman, a professor of finance at Santa Clara University in California, concluded the same thing, that socially responsible funds tend to have higher annual fees, so their returns are likely to lag behind over time. And that's a huge issue. And one more 401k investors need to be aware of because fees eat away over time. At our retirement savings, which can impact your long-term retirement income. It doesn't matter if we're talking ESG funds or target day funds, investors need to know how much they're paying in fees, period.",
